==Old English==
===Etymology===
Cognate with Old Saxon [[rakud]] (used of the Temple of Jerusalem).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'reʧed/

===Noun===
'''reċed''' ''n''
# ''(Poetic)'' a [[hall]]; a [[house]] or [[building]]
#:''Duru sceal on healle, rum recedes muð'': Door shall be in hall, building's broad mouth.  (''Maxims II'')

